WEBVTT

00:01.511 --> 00:03.412
Previously on Nancy Drew...

00:03.813 --> 00:07.311
ACE: Lucy Sable was crowned
Sea Queen in the year 2000.

00:07.355 --> 00:09.357
Disappeared after the
celebration, never seen again.

00:09.400 --> 00:10.836
[fireworks popping, whistling]

00:10.880 --> 00:12.142
Never had a murder
pinned on her, though.

00:12.186 --> 00:14.057
McGINNIS:
Nancy Drew. She used to

00:14.101 --> 00:15.189
complicate my job.

00:15.232 --> 00:16.233
And for the rest of you,

00:16.277 --> 00:20.020
city girl, ex-con,
town screwup...

00:20.063 --> 00:21.456
NANCY:
Once a year, the town gathers

00:21.499 --> 00:23.023
for the bucket ritual. [crowd cheering]

00:23.066 --> 00:25.634
Get a bucket of seawater,
put it outside your door.

00:25.677 --> 00:27.592
Kick it over.

00:27.636 --> 00:29.464
If it's turned to blood,
you're marked to die

00:29.507 --> 00:31.379
in the coming year.
GEORGE: Are they gonna do an autopsy?

00:31.422 --> 00:34.034
I overheard that the Hudson
family got a judge to block it.

00:34.077 --> 00:35.339
They're moving the body tonight.

00:35.383 --> 00:37.080
If we had someone,

00:37.124 --> 00:39.039
a forensic chemist,
he could perform

00:39.082 --> 00:42.477
the same kind of
toxicology test for you.

00:42.520 --> 00:44.044
It-it may not be a full autopsy,

00:44.087 --> 00:46.394
but it could be enough to
figure out how Tiffany died.

00:46.437 --> 00:48.744
Hello, Tiffany.

00:50.137 --> 00:52.052
[siren blaring]
CARSON: They're charging you

00:52.095 --> 00:55.055
with burglary
and criminal trespass.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.491
This girl detective stuff

00:56.534 --> 00:58.058
isn't cute anymore.

00:58.101 --> 00:59.624
And what are you doing
with Ned Nickerson?

00:59.668 --> 01:01.365
Stay away from that kid.

01:01.409 --> 01:03.715
NANCY:
Let's see who Tiffany texted
right before she died.

01:03.759 --> 01:06.283
[line ringing]

01:17.164 --> 01:21.124
♪ Oh, oh-oh ♪

01:21.168 --> 01:22.299
♪ Oh ♪

01:22.343 --> 01:24.736
♪ Oh-oh ♪

01:24.780 --> 01:28.914
♪ Oh, oh-oh ♪

01:28.958 --> 01:30.090
♪ Oh ♪

01:30.133 --> 01:32.788
♪ Oh-oh-oh ♪

01:32.831 --> 01:34.094
♪ Oh ♪

01:34.137 --> 01:38.010
♪ Oh-oh ♪

01:38.054 --> 01:41.188
♪ I've given my words to you ♪
[thunder rumbling]

01:41.231 --> 01:43.103
♪ I'd do it again ♪

01:45.148 --> 01:49.109
♪ You know them by heart by now ♪

01:49.152 --> 01:52.155
♪ You have them within... ♪

01:52.199 --> 01:54.679
[chanting]:
Om...

01:59.075 --> 02:00.729
Om...

02:00.772 --> 02:02.861
♪ ♪

02:11.957 --> 02:14.134
You won
the blood bucket challenge.

02:14.177 --> 02:16.310
[exhales]
I got punked, okay?

02:16.353 --> 02:17.920
You want help?

02:22.185 --> 02:24.231
[thunder cracking]

02:26.189 --> 02:27.582
That'll help.

02:34.284 --> 02:35.894
Oh, no, not again!

02:39.985 --> 02:41.291
[water continues dripping]

02:43.293 --> 02:46.166
Don't move.
I'll get us some coffee.

02:46.209 --> 02:49.778
That's usually mycontribution.

02:49.821 --> 02:52.259
Not today.

02:55.479 --> 02:57.481
[thunder rumbling]

03:06.795 --> 03:10.190
NANCY:
I'm sure there are plenty
of logical explanations

03:10.233 --> 03:12.801
why a mechanic would have
two cell phones.

03:23.290 --> 03:27.250
Unfortunately, only one reason
why this mystery phone

03:27.294 --> 03:29.470
would show
a missed call from me,

03:29.513 --> 03:32.864
and the final text
that Tiffany sent.

03:35.258 --> 03:37.521
And my mom's car?

03:39.436 --> 03:41.308
See if we can get
this thing running again.

03:47.923 --> 03:49.359
Didn't push the plunger yet.

03:49.403 --> 03:51.405
I should know
how strong you take it.

03:51.448 --> 03:53.450
[phone vibrating]

04:01.284 --> 04:02.720
There's only one other caller

04:02.764 --> 04:04.853
logged on that phone, Nick.

04:05.941 --> 04:07.334
Tiffany Hudson.

04:07.377 --> 04:09.249
She sent you a text

04:09.292 --> 04:11.207
right before she died.

04:11.251 --> 04:12.774
You knew her.

04:12.817 --> 04:14.819
Why would you
keep that a secret?

04:16.343 --> 04:17.605
I have a record.

04:17.648 --> 04:19.955
You know what happens
if the police tie me to her?

04:19.998 --> 04:21.261
The cops I get.

04:21.304 --> 04:23.175
But you kept it a secret
from me.

04:23.219 --> 04:25.526
Nancy, I had nothing to do with
Tiffany's death. You know that.

04:25.569 --> 04:26.744
Here's what I know:

04:26.788 --> 04:29.747
Tiffany Hudson's testimony
put you in jail.

04:29.791 --> 04:31.836
You did two years
for manslaughter.

04:31.880 --> 04:33.055
How did you learn that? I...

04:33.098 --> 04:34.361
I saw my dad's file on you.

04:34.404 --> 04:37.015
Somehow, you were in
contact with Tiffany.

04:37.059 --> 04:39.148
The last text she sent
was about a package

04:39.191 --> 04:42.282
in my mom's car, which you
got access to through me.

04:44.109 --> 04:45.807
Were you using me?

04:45.850 --> 04:47.199
No. I would never.

04:47.243 --> 04:49.419
[chuckles]
How am I supposed to believe that?

04:51.334 --> 04:52.814
Now's the time, Nick.

04:52.857 --> 04:56.731
If you ever want there
to be any trust between us,

04:56.774 --> 04:59.211
show me what you took
from my mom's car.

04:59.255 --> 05:00.778
I can't.

05:02.432 --> 05:03.999
It's not for you.

05:10.005 --> 05:12.007
My dad was right about you.

05:13.008 --> 05:15.010
♪ ♪

05:25.107 --> 05:27.544
[thunder rumbling]

05:27.588 --> 05:29.590
♪ ♪

05:35.378 --> 05:36.640
Waited up for you last night.

05:36.684 --> 05:38.207
You don't have
to do that anymore.

05:38.250 --> 05:39.643
I'm not a kid.

05:39.687 --> 05:42.342
Where did you sleep?

05:42.385 --> 05:44.344
I was at a friend's house.

05:44.387 --> 05:46.302
Can we be honest
with each other?

05:46.346 --> 05:48.391
[chuckles] Sure.

05:50.175 --> 05:51.699
What happened
to the bloody dress

05:51.742 --> 05:53.353
that used to be in the attic?

05:53.396 --> 05:54.441
I threw it away.

05:54.484 --> 05:56.443
It was part
of an old, dumb joke.

05:56.486 --> 05:59.359
It's not in any of
our trash cans. I checked.

05:59.402 --> 06:03.363
The trash got picked up
this morning.

06:03.406 --> 06:06.409
Nancy, what are you doing?

06:06.453 --> 06:09.238
Sneaking around,
digging through trash cans?

06:10.457 --> 06:12.676
You're about to be arraigned
on felony charges

06:12.720 --> 06:15.287
for burglary and trespassing
at the morgue.

06:15.331 --> 06:16.811
You need to be putting
your best foot forward

06:16.854 --> 06:18.116
with the judge.

06:18.160 --> 06:20.205
Is it possible that you can
keep out of trouble

06:20.249 --> 06:21.424
for the next few days?

06:21.468 --> 06:23.034
I'll do my best, counselor.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.732
Anything else you need to relay?

06:25.820 --> 06:27.430
You're right.
You're not a kid.

06:28.736 --> 06:30.477
But you're still mykid.

06:30.520 --> 06:32.435
[doorbell rings]

06:32.479 --> 06:34.568
[thunder rumbles]

06:34.611 --> 06:36.134
I have a client.

06:39.355 --> 06:40.922
Where's Tiffany's will?

06:40.965 --> 06:42.619
RYAN:
Uh, we had a prenup.

06:42.663 --> 06:44.273
It covered her estate planning.

06:44.316 --> 06:45.492
Um, basically, what
was hers was hers,

06:45.535 --> 06:46.884
and what was mine was mine.

06:46.928 --> 06:48.712
But it should all go to me
as soon as they confirm

06:48.756 --> 06:50.322
that she died of natural causes.

06:50.366 --> 06:52.150
Are you worried she didn'tdie
of natural causes?

06:52.194 --> 06:53.195
No.

06:54.370 --> 06:55.415
No, what I'm worried about

06:55.458 --> 06:56.894
is how I'm gonna
make these payments.

06:56.938 --> 06:58.505
So, can you just

06:58.548 --> 07:00.376
tell me what-what of this I can

07:00.420 --> 07:01.769
touch right now?

07:01.812 --> 07:04.293
[sighs heavily] Well...

07:05.555 --> 07:06.774
[wood creaking]

07:06.817 --> 07:08.950
[sighs] Okay.

07:08.993 --> 07:10.952
Hey.

07:11.996 --> 07:13.476
Hey.

07:13.520 --> 07:15.173
We've met, haven't we?

07:15.217 --> 07:17.219
Ryan, this is my daughter Nancy.

07:18.655 --> 07:20.440
Chief McGinnis
told me about you.

07:20.483 --> 07:23.834
[chuckles]
He called you the town snoop.

07:23.878 --> 07:26.533
Well, I live here.
So I wasn't snooping.

07:26.576 --> 07:27.969
NANCY:
I totally was.

07:30.014 --> 07:31.799
Have a good day at work.

07:31.842 --> 07:34.671
Yes, sir. Nice to meet you.

07:36.804 --> 07:39.502
All righty.[thunder rumbles]

07:39.546 --> 07:41.504
Shift started
nine minutes ago, Drew.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.550
Got to dock you this time.

07:45.116 --> 07:48.293
[sighs]
George is extra prickly today.

07:48.337 --> 07:50.295
She kicked a blood bucket.

07:50.339 --> 07:52.254
So the curse says
she'll be dead inside a year.

07:52.297 --> 07:54.517
Wait, you saw it? Yeah.

07:54.561 --> 07:56.476
There's a lot of it.
It'll ruin your morning.

07:56.519 --> 07:58.478
Please. George doesn't
believe in curses.

07:58.521 --> 08:01.089
It's the one thing
we agree on. Then she's probably

08:01.132 --> 08:04.179
worried about the nor'easter
storm that's coming.

08:04.222 --> 08:05.833
The locals tell tales.

08:05.876 --> 08:07.487
Tales as in fictional stories.

08:07.530 --> 08:10.359
Yeah, okay.About...

08:10.402 --> 08:13.536
how the nor'easter
blows restless spirits ashore.

08:13.580 --> 08:16.104
Oh, dear.[entry bell jingles]

08:16.147 --> 08:17.758
I'll get it.

08:17.801 --> 08:20.500
You're not afraid to eat here?

08:20.543 --> 08:22.937
Our lab tested all the food
from the Claw

08:22.980 --> 08:23.981
the night Tiffany died.

08:24.025 --> 08:25.417
No traces of poison anywhere.

08:25.461 --> 08:27.376
Great.
We'll post about it on Yelp.

08:27.419 --> 08:29.421
Karen, why are you really here?

08:35.166 --> 08:38.343
Based on her 911 call, the
D.A.'s looking to build a case

08:38.387 --> 08:39.780
out of Tiffany Hudson's death.

08:39.823 --> 08:42.217
Your break-in at the morgue
makes you look like

08:42.260 --> 08:43.566
a pretty good suspect,

08:43.610 --> 08:45.481
if your criminal charges stand.

08:47.135 --> 08:49.398
But we have a new suspect.

08:49.441 --> 08:51.139
And I'm betting
that you can give us

08:51.182 --> 08:53.533
information that could
lead to his arrest.

08:58.407 --> 09:00.191
You want Nick.

09:00.235 --> 09:02.063
He's got a criminal record.

09:02.106 --> 09:04.456
We got the protective order
lifted and uncovered a motive.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.632
So when they say

09:05.675 --> 09:06.894
juvenile records are sealed,

09:06.937 --> 09:08.504
guess they don't mean
sealedsealed.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.288
I know you didn't kill Tiffany.

09:10.332 --> 09:12.552
If you give me something
on Nick,

09:12.595 --> 09:14.554
enough to take the interest
off of you,

09:14.597 --> 09:16.904
your criminal charges go away.

09:18.862 --> 09:20.124
You don't want
a felony conviction

09:20.168 --> 09:21.909
on your college
applications, Nance.

09:21.952 --> 09:24.041
I'll give you till

09:24.085 --> 09:26.304
the end of day.

09:31.092 --> 09:32.484
Stay safe, everyone.

09:32.528 --> 09:35.052
Feels like a nor'easter
spinning up.

09:37.751 --> 09:40.144
The cops think Nick
killed Tiffany?

09:40.188 --> 09:41.581
She said motive.

09:41.624 --> 09:43.539
Something about
his juvenile conviction?

09:43.583 --> 09:44.932
BESS:
Wait, did he do something violent?

09:44.975 --> 09:46.455
Like how violent?

09:46.498 --> 09:48.109
Like assault?
Robbery?

09:48.152 --> 09:49.327
Manslaughter?

09:49.371 --> 09:50.502
Did he kill someone?

09:50.546 --> 09:52.156
No, manslaughter's different.

09:52.200 --> 09:53.636
But he did kill someone?

09:53.680 --> 09:55.333
I don't... have all the facts.

09:55.377 --> 09:56.900
He-he never told me
what happened.

09:56.944 --> 09:58.467
GEORGE:
Okay, we're missing the silver lining here.

09:58.510 --> 09:59.599
If Nick did kill Tiffany,

09:59.642 --> 10:01.383
we're all off the hook
as suspects.

10:01.426 --> 10:02.689
That's a little harsh. So?

10:02.732 --> 10:04.299
You get a clean slate,
all my customers return,

10:04.342 --> 10:06.475
and then Bess can go back
to being a carefree rich girl

10:06.518 --> 10:07.650
slumming as a subpar waitress.

10:07.694 --> 10:09.043
Ah. You said
I was improving.

10:09.086 --> 10:10.348
Pretty low bar.

10:10.392 --> 10:12.307
What made the cops look at Nick?

10:12.350 --> 10:14.918
[phone vibrating,
thunder rumbling]

10:23.013 --> 10:25.320
What's with the secrecy? The cops just

10:25.363 --> 10:26.364
tossed my place.

10:26.408 --> 10:28.323
What? They had
a search warrant.

10:28.366 --> 10:31.326
Said they triangulated
recent calls to the burner phone

10:31.369 --> 10:33.197
that Tiffany sent
a text message to.

10:33.241 --> 10:35.373
They were looking
for the phone... I took it.

10:37.462 --> 10:38.855
And deactivated it.

10:38.899 --> 10:40.378
You know you're supposed to burn

10:40.422 --> 10:41.771
a burner phone
when it's done, right?

10:41.815 --> 10:43.686
I couldn't lose the
text history with Tiffany.

10:43.730 --> 10:46.123
I've been studying every word,

10:46.167 --> 10:48.343
looking for clues, because...

11:00.398 --> 11:02.662
This is what
was in your mom's car.

11:02.705 --> 11:04.968
And Tiffany told me
not to trust anyone.

11:05.012 --> 11:07.841
But I've been staring at
this thing for two days now,

11:07.884 --> 11:10.060
and I still don't know
what its purpose is.

11:10.104 --> 11:12.019
You brought me a puzzle.

11:13.585 --> 11:16.110
If I solve this, will I either
want to forgive him

11:16.153 --> 11:17.720
or put him away?

11:17.764 --> 11:19.374
Let's figure it out.

11:28.165 --> 11:31.038
So, there's either
something inside it,

11:31.081 --> 11:34.041
or it's meant
to lead us somewhere.

11:34.084 --> 11:36.260
[sighs] Tiffany loved
her hidden treasures.

11:36.304 --> 11:38.741
Emphasis on hidden.

11:38.785 --> 11:42.266
It seemed like she had a lot
of enemies in this town.

11:42.310 --> 11:44.442
So that's why she turned to you?

11:46.836 --> 11:48.142
[sighs]

11:49.970 --> 11:51.928
Why was this in my mom's car?

11:51.972 --> 11:54.235
Your mom was my social worker.

11:54.278 --> 11:57.281
She started out helping
your dad on my case;

11:57.325 --> 12:00.284
then after I got sentenced,

12:00.328 --> 12:02.504
she'd come and visit me.

12:02.547 --> 12:05.159
Did you know who I was?[thunder rumbling]

12:05.202 --> 12:06.900
Before we met
on the Fourth of July?

12:06.943 --> 12:08.902
Yes.

12:08.945 --> 12:10.381
But I wasn't trying
to get to the car.

12:10.425 --> 12:12.601
I just wanted to meet you
because your mom was

12:12.644 --> 12:13.950
one of the only
good people I knew

12:13.994 --> 12:15.343
during that time in my life.

12:15.386 --> 12:17.171
But this package
was from Tiffany.

12:17.214 --> 12:19.303
You got to help me understand.

12:19.347 --> 12:20.870
[thunder cracks]

12:22.698 --> 12:24.656
[sighs]

12:24.700 --> 12:26.180
When I was doing time,

12:26.223 --> 12:27.834
if anyone but Kate Drew

12:27.877 --> 12:30.750
had asked me to meet the witness
who got me locked up,

12:30.793 --> 12:32.273
no way I'd have agreed.

12:32.316 --> 12:33.840
But your mom...

12:36.016 --> 12:37.539
[sighs]
She was different.

12:37.582 --> 12:40.237
She could wear you down
with kindness.

12:40.281 --> 12:43.458
Yeah. She really could.

12:43.501 --> 12:46.678
So, finally I told her she could
send Tiffany for a visit.

12:46.722 --> 12:48.724
[clock ticking]

12:51.074 --> 12:52.989
NICK:
I was mad, caged.

12:53.033 --> 12:54.991
I mean, it was hard enough just
to sit across from this person.

12:55.035 --> 12:57.428
No force on earth
could make me talk to her.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.779
[door buzzes]

12:59.822 --> 13:02.303
I let the time pass
without a word.

13:04.784 --> 13:06.307
[door opens]

13:06.350 --> 13:07.917
And she came back the next week,

13:07.961 --> 13:09.353
like it was my job

13:09.397 --> 13:11.486
to ease her guilt
for testifying against me.

13:11.529 --> 13:14.924
I passed another hour
not hearing a word she said.

13:14.968 --> 13:17.318
So she found another way.

13:18.580 --> 13:21.844
You communicated through books?

13:21.888 --> 13:24.368
She called it our
secret language.

13:25.369 --> 13:27.415
[thunder rumbling]

13:29.721 --> 13:31.506
RITA:
Hello?

13:32.942 --> 13:34.770
Welcome to the Claw. [gasps]

13:34.814 --> 13:36.859
George, oh, my God!

13:36.903 --> 13:39.122
You could've got a
shard in your neck.

13:39.166 --> 13:40.167
You're cursed.
You're cursed.

13:40.210 --> 13:42.778
Oh, don't say that.
I'm fine.

13:42.822 --> 13:44.388
Is this a bad time?

13:44.432 --> 13:45.737
I was hoping you were hiring.

13:45.781 --> 13:47.261
I can take care of you.

13:48.653 --> 13:50.133
I got it.

13:50.177 --> 13:53.223
I'm Rita.Ah. Hi, Rita.

13:53.267 --> 13:55.182
So have you ever
waited tables before?

13:55.225 --> 13:58.489
Once. On roller skates.

13:58.533 --> 14:00.796
[gasps] Oh, I love
those retro places.

14:00.840 --> 14:03.016
I'll get a dustpan.
[sighs]Yeah.

14:06.454 --> 14:08.804
[gasping]

14:08.848 --> 14:10.458
Oh, my gosh.

14:10.501 --> 14:11.981
Damn, that curse is alive.

14:12.025 --> 14:13.417
I don't believe in curses.

14:13.461 --> 14:14.505
Well, then explain that!

14:14.549 --> 14:16.464
Gravity!

14:16.507 --> 14:18.509
[thunder rumbling]

14:23.558 --> 14:25.560
♪ ♪

14:28.563 --> 14:30.565
Did you see there's
an engraving in here?

14:33.785 --> 14:36.919
It's too long
to be a serial number,

14:36.963 --> 14:38.965
too new to be a smith's mark.

14:40.792 --> 14:43.447
If books were your secret
language, maybe it's an ISBN.

14:43.491 --> 14:46.102
You know, the number
on the cover of books.

14:46.146 --> 14:48.670
Did you keep the ones
she gave you?

14:53.066 --> 14:55.459
It's a protection circle.
ACE: This is Rita.

14:55.503 --> 14:57.070
We found a how-to
video on the Internet.

14:57.113 --> 14:58.941
BESS:
The blood bucket is obviously trying

14:58.985 --> 15:00.464
to kill George.

15:00.508 --> 15:03.119
Obviously.
Where are you two going?

15:03.163 --> 15:05.861
We're gonna follow clues from a dead woman.
Ooh, like a treasure hunt?

15:05.905 --> 15:07.428
No.
GEORGE: Drew, you're going outside,

15:07.471 --> 15:08.995
right now? With him?

15:09.038 --> 15:10.648
Why can't this wait?

15:13.086 --> 15:15.262
It's time-sensitive.

15:17.003 --> 15:18.830
[thunder rumbling]

15:20.267 --> 15:22.530
There must be something
in your books.

15:24.662 --> 15:27.317
Clock wasn't the first thing
Tiffany gave me.

15:29.015 --> 15:30.668
That would be this.

15:34.629 --> 15:37.632
"But my real treasure
are the rays of intelligence

15:37.675 --> 15:39.503
you have elicited from my brain..."

15:39.547 --> 15:40.678
[door buzzes]

15:40.722 --> 15:43.029
"...the languages you have implanted

15:43.072 --> 15:45.248
in my memory."

15:45.292 --> 15:47.163
The books got me talking,
but the story

15:47.207 --> 15:49.644
she really wanted to hear
was my own.

15:49.687 --> 15:52.560
You weren't inside the party.

15:52.603 --> 15:56.564
I know you were on the
sidewalk at 8:12 p.m.

15:56.607 --> 15:58.566
Now, you heard the sound.

15:58.609 --> 16:00.611
[glass breaks, thud]

16:03.832 --> 16:06.574
After a few months,
I asked for newer books.

16:06.617 --> 16:09.577
Toni Morrison, Ntozake Shange.

16:09.620 --> 16:12.536
Had to get past Edith Wharton.
Man, that was a slog.

16:12.580 --> 16:13.973
House of Mirthmy ass.

16:14.016 --> 16:15.496
Under the Lilacs.

16:15.539 --> 16:17.150
The, uh...

16:17.193 --> 16:18.586
The number's almost the same.

16:18.629 --> 16:19.935
If you lop off the
first three digits,

16:19.979 --> 16:21.415
the last 13 line up.

16:21.458 --> 16:23.156
First three digits
are one, seven, zero.

16:23.199 --> 16:24.592
Page 170.

16:24.635 --> 16:27.551
Chapter title:
"A Boy's Bargain."

16:27.595 --> 16:31.120
Oh, uh, a bargain has
two sides. It's not a gift.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.122
You got to meet in the middle.

16:33.166 --> 16:35.777
Under the Lilacs.

16:35.820 --> 16:38.823
[sighs]
Tiffany loved puzzles and-and

16:38.867 --> 16:40.173
escape rooms and plays on words.

16:40.216 --> 16:41.565
And she knew
you'd remember that,

16:41.609 --> 16:42.914
so whatever trail she left,

16:42.958 --> 16:44.699
it has to be one
that you can follow.

16:44.742 --> 16:47.832
There was someplace she loved
here in town. Lilac something.

16:53.360 --> 16:54.752
I think I know where to go.

16:56.189 --> 16:59.061
But we're gonna need
some help first.

16:59.105 --> 17:02.673
♪ Good love, got to get a piece of it ♪

17:03.674 --> 17:06.068
♪ Showstopping fire ♪

17:06.112 --> 17:08.679
♪ Making your jaw hit the floor ♪

17:08.723 --> 17:10.899
♪ Got to feed that desire ♪

17:10.942 --> 17:13.728
♪ Keep you coming back for more ♪

17:13.771 --> 17:17.036
♪ Got to get it, got to get it now ♪

17:17.079 --> 17:19.603
♪ If you want it, got to go get it now ♪

17:19.647 --> 17:22.780
♪ Got to get it, got to get it, yeah ♪

17:24.652 --> 17:26.610
♪ Got to get it, got to get it ♪

17:26.654 --> 17:28.090
[siren whoops]
♪ Now, if you want it ♪

17:28.134 --> 17:29.657
♪ Got to go get it now ♪

17:29.700 --> 17:32.660
♪ Got to get it, got to get it, yeah ♪

17:36.011 --> 17:38.970
♪ Oh, get it now... ♪

17:39.014 --> 17:40.972
Is there a problem, Detective?

17:43.018 --> 17:46.717
Get off the roads.
Told you it's not safe out here.

17:46.761 --> 17:48.676
Okay.

17:48.719 --> 17:51.026
♪ Got to get it, got to get it, yeah ♪

17:53.550 --> 17:55.726
♪ Got to get it, got to get it now ♪

17:55.770 --> 17:58.120
♪ If you want it, got to go get it now ♪

17:58.164 --> 18:00.122
♪ Got to get it, got to get it, yeah ♪

18:00.166 --> 18:01.906
♪ If you want it, got to go get it now. ♪

18:08.783 --> 18:10.785
[thunder rumbling]

18:13.788 --> 18:16.747
CARSON:
What do you know about the Lilac Inn?

18:16.791 --> 18:20.360
That old B and B
over on Horseshoe Point?

18:20.403 --> 18:22.101
[sighs] Not much.

18:22.144 --> 18:24.407
It was, uh, Tiff's pet project.

18:24.451 --> 18:26.583
She was restoring it.

18:26.627 --> 18:28.194
Dumped a bunch of money into it

18:28.237 --> 18:30.587
that I could really
use right now.[thudding]

18:30.631 --> 18:33.416
What's your concern
about your finances?[wood creaking]

18:33.460 --> 18:36.593
I'm not seeing any large
payments due anytime soon.

18:36.637 --> 18:37.681
I thought your daughter
left the house.

18:37.725 --> 18:39.683
Uh-huh.

18:39.727 --> 18:43.252
It looks like
she's got this Lilac Inn

18:43.296 --> 18:46.037
approved for landmark status.

18:50.259 --> 18:52.261
[thudding continues]

18:55.699 --> 18:57.701
[wood creaking]

19:03.751 --> 19:05.622
[scratching on wood]

19:05.666 --> 19:07.624
[wind whistling]

19:07.668 --> 19:09.670
[thudding continues]

19:11.802 --> 19:13.804
[thudding continues
louder, faster]

19:19.070 --> 19:21.072
[wind groaning, whistling]

19:24.250 --> 19:26.382
[thunder rumbling]

19:29.080 --> 19:30.560
[gasps]

19:30.604 --> 19:32.171
What are you doing up here?

19:32.214 --> 19:33.563
[panting]

19:33.607 --> 19:35.130
I, uh...

19:35.174 --> 19:36.784
I thought I heard something.

19:36.827 --> 19:39.178
No, we're alone.Yeah.

19:39.221 --> 19:42.181
Hey, have you been
self-medicating?

19:43.965 --> 19:46.620
No, it's just the, um...

19:46.663 --> 19:49.362
storm's getting to my-my head.

19:49.405 --> 19:51.407
All right, come on.

19:53.801 --> 19:57.805
Based on the paperwork,
it looks like this Lilac Inn

19:57.848 --> 20:00.851
is being turned into
a public landmark.

20:00.895 --> 20:02.636
Wait, what? No.

20:02.679 --> 20:04.855
I thought she was flipping it.
We were gonna sell it.

20:04.899 --> 20:06.553
No, approval's gone through.

20:06.596 --> 20:08.685
[thudding resumes]After they wrap
up final touches,

20:08.729 --> 20:10.557
you won't have any
claim to it anymore,

20:10.600 --> 20:12.820
and that could happen

20:12.863 --> 20:15.692
soon as this storm clears.

20:17.041 --> 20:18.956
Ryan? Do you not hear

20:19.000 --> 20:20.828
those footsteps upstairs?

20:22.133 --> 20:24.005
[scoffs]

20:24.048 --> 20:26.225
Okay, um...
[clears throat]

20:26.268 --> 20:28.444
Look, before Tiffany died,
she was...

20:28.488 --> 20:30.794
she was waking up
in the middle of the night,

20:30.838 --> 20:33.797
saying that she thought
someone was watching us sleep,

20:33.841 --> 20:36.060
that... walking around
in the bedroom.

20:36.104 --> 20:37.801
You know, and I just...
[chuckles]

20:37.845 --> 20:40.369
I thought it was her anxiety
meds, to be honest with you.

20:40.413 --> 20:41.675
[Lucy shrieks]

20:41.718 --> 20:43.720
What the hell?

20:43.764 --> 20:45.635
Okay, that's it.
I'm out of here.

20:45.679 --> 20:47.028
Whoa, hang on. Hey!

20:47.071 --> 20:48.812
Hang on.
You're not driving anywhere.

20:48.856 --> 20:50.510
The last thing you need
is a DUI.

20:50.553 --> 20:53.034
Okay, well, then you take me to
Tiffany's place, the Lilac Inn.

20:53.077 --> 20:54.905
Have you seen the roads outside?

20:54.949 --> 20:57.299
You got a dad car. You're fine.
Come on, get your coat.

20:57.343 --> 20:58.866
[sighs]

21:04.350 --> 21:05.786
[gasps]

21:05.829 --> 21:07.266
ACE:
Someone's gonna have

21:07.309 --> 21:10.181
a bad day when they find
that branch through the window.

21:11.835 --> 21:13.837
Oh, my God. You all right?

21:13.881 --> 21:16.753
Yeah. I'm fine.

21:20.366 --> 21:22.542
Tiffany told me
about her fixer-uppers.

21:22.585 --> 21:24.979
She definitely believed in the
possibility of transformation.

21:25.022 --> 21:27.242
After you told her your story?

21:27.286 --> 21:29.636
You did tell her, right?

21:29.679 --> 21:31.638
Eventually.

21:31.681 --> 21:33.901
This looks like
Robert Louis Stevenson.

21:33.944 --> 21:35.685
Treasure Island.

21:37.034 --> 21:39.167
I think this is E.B. White.

21:39.210 --> 21:41.212
Charlotte's Web.

21:42.866 --> 21:44.955
Beardo is Longfellow.

21:44.999 --> 21:48.002
And they're both Mainers,
so this last one's got to be

21:48.045 --> 21:50.004
Stephen King.

21:50.047 --> 21:52.006
Or not.

21:52.049 --> 21:54.922
Nick, what did you tell Tiffany

21:54.965 --> 21:56.663
about the night it happened?

21:59.927 --> 22:04.932
The guy I hurt, we were
part of a spring break trip.

22:04.975 --> 22:07.456
Bunch of stupid kids
from high school

22:07.500 --> 22:10.024
up in the sticks of Maine
for a football camp.

22:10.067 --> 22:14.550
Uh, this one guy,
we got into it one night.

22:14.594 --> 22:16.552
Tiffany saw how it ended.

22:16.596 --> 22:19.903
She wanted to know
how it started, so I told her.

22:19.947 --> 22:21.905
Afterwards,

22:21.949 --> 22:24.908
she told me she wished
she could take it all back,

22:24.952 --> 22:27.650
like, if she could
turn back time,

22:27.694 --> 22:29.304
she could've changed my life.

22:29.348 --> 22:31.959
How did the fight start?

22:32.002 --> 22:33.917
I'm just trying to solve this.

22:33.961 --> 22:36.180
No, it feels more like
you're trying to solve me

22:36.224 --> 22:37.747
than Tiffany's puzzle.

22:37.791 --> 22:38.966
I'm on your side.

22:39.009 --> 22:40.576
Doing what, exactly?

22:40.620 --> 22:42.926
Digging into places I've asked
you not to go? And for what?

22:42.970 --> 22:45.276
You haven't told me
the details of what happened.

22:45.320 --> 22:46.495
If I knew the circumstances,

22:46.539 --> 22:48.541
I could try to understand
how something...

22:48.584 --> 22:50.369
How what?
I could take someone's life?

22:51.979 --> 22:54.111
It was self-defense.
Why do you care how it happened?

22:54.155 --> 22:56.984
Because I need to know
what you're capable of.

22:57.027 --> 22:58.377
Do you think I killed Tiffany?

22:59.508 --> 23:01.336
Do you think
I could murder someone

23:01.380 --> 23:03.643
in cold blood?

23:03.686 --> 23:05.035
[vehicle approaching]

23:05.079 --> 23:07.734
[thunder rumbling]

23:13.087 --> 23:15.089
Oh, God,
it's my father and Ryan.

23:15.132 --> 23:17.004
It's Edith Wharton.

23:17.047 --> 23:19.006
It's The House ofdamn Mirth.

23:19.049 --> 23:21.051
We need to hide.

23:22.531 --> 23:24.707
She's telling me
it's in the kitchen.

23:33.020 --> 23:34.282
Nick, we cannot
get caught in here.

23:34.325 --> 23:35.936
Are you that ashamed
of having your father

23:35.979 --> 23:37.764
see you here with me?
He's Ryan's lawyer now.

23:37.807 --> 23:39.461
I don't want either of them
to find out what we're doing.

23:39.505 --> 23:40.941
Plus, Tiffany went
to a lot of trouble

23:40.984 --> 23:42.812
to keep this clock a secret
from her husband.

23:42.856 --> 23:44.945
"How delicious to have a place
like this all to one's self."

23:44.988 --> 23:46.033
What are you saying?

23:46.076 --> 23:48.252
Uh, not my words.
Uh, Wharton's.

23:48.296 --> 23:50.472
Tiffany loved this part.

23:50.516 --> 23:55.042
Loved all the little
cakes... in cupboards.

23:58.524 --> 24:00.439
NANCY:
Quick, we need to hide.

24:03.006 --> 24:05.008
RYAN:
This is unbelievable.

24:10.100 --> 24:11.972
Maybe we could strip it
for parts. You know?

24:12.015 --> 24:14.017
There's got to be 100 grand
worth of vintage hardware alone.

24:16.106 --> 24:19.066
It's an odd clause
in your prenup

24:19.109 --> 24:21.372
that the only way
you inherit her estate

24:21.416 --> 24:23.984
is if Tiffany died
of natural causes.

24:24.027 --> 24:25.551
Tiffany was a perfectly
healthy young woman.

24:25.594 --> 24:27.509
What makes you think
her death was natural?

24:27.553 --> 24:29.511
She wasn't healthy, Carson.

24:29.555 --> 24:31.426
She was taking a whole cocktail

24:31.470 --> 24:33.428
full of mood stabilizers
and sleeping pills.

24:33.472 --> 24:36.300
It's what made her so paranoid,
seeing things.

24:36.344 --> 24:37.998
That's why she put
the clause in.

24:38.041 --> 24:41.828
Like I or anybody else
wanted her dead.

24:41.871 --> 24:44.395
[thunder rumbling]

24:44.439 --> 24:48.399
Look, I don't know
how she died, okay?

24:48.443 --> 24:50.401
I mean, m-maybe...

24:50.445 --> 24:52.229
Do you think maybe
she was haunted?

24:53.361 --> 24:55.537
That's a... a literal question?

24:55.581 --> 25:00.107
You-you think she was haunted,
by ghosts?

25:00.150 --> 25:03.110
I don't know. Maybe.
You know? I mean, I...

25:03.153 --> 25:05.025
I mean, do you,
do you think that

25:05.068 --> 25:07.027
w-we're visited by
vengeful spirits?

25:07.070 --> 25:09.682
You know, forces
that are trying to harm us?

25:09.725 --> 25:12.032
I've heard that theory. Yeah, well,
Tiffany sure did.

25:12.075 --> 25:16.210
That's why she spent so much of
her energy trying to make good.

25:16.253 --> 25:18.865
Well, if those were her wishes,

25:18.908 --> 25:21.041
it argues for leaving
this place alone.

25:21.084 --> 25:23.522
Yeah, except
I need my money now.

25:23.565 --> 25:25.001
Who do you owe?

25:32.400 --> 25:35.359
It's best to leave
the bodies buried.

25:35.403 --> 25:37.405
Figuratively, this time.

25:41.627 --> 25:43.106
[sighs]

25:45.108 --> 25:47.110
[wood creaking]

25:50.374 --> 25:54.074
[exhales, shivering]

25:54.117 --> 25:56.076
Nick, are you all right? Ah, yeah.

25:56.119 --> 25:58.513
My jail cell was cramped
like this. I'm not a big fan

25:58.557 --> 26:00.080
of small spaces.

26:00.123 --> 26:02.212
Hey. Nick, look at me.

26:02.256 --> 26:04.563
Hey. It's okay.

26:04.606 --> 26:06.129
No, I can't be in here.

26:07.653 --> 26:10.612
Just calm down. What, you're
afraid of me now?

26:10.656 --> 26:12.266
'Cause of what I did to Austin?

26:12.309 --> 26:13.572
Austin.

26:13.615 --> 26:15.617
Was that his name? Yeah.

26:15.661 --> 26:18.489
H-He's the one
you told Tiffany about.

26:18.533 --> 26:19.882
She helped you, with the,

26:19.926 --> 26:22.102
with the books she gave you.
She believed in you.

26:22.145 --> 26:23.843
How did she reach you?

26:23.886 --> 26:25.148
She wanted me to move on.

26:25.192 --> 26:26.802
You-you want to
send me back there.

26:26.846 --> 26:28.195
No, no. I don't.

26:28.238 --> 26:30.240
I just want you
to be here with me.

26:30.284 --> 26:32.895
Okay? Just be here with me.

26:32.939 --> 26:34.201
Please.

26:34.244 --> 26:37.247
[panting]

26:39.293 --> 26:42.426
What? What is it?

26:42.470 --> 26:44.864
"Amontillado."

26:44.907 --> 26:46.605
A... wha... a what?

26:52.959 --> 26:57.050
If "under the lilacs" didn't do it,

26:57.093 --> 27:01.184
or they took down every
portrait, there's no way

27:01.228 --> 27:03.709
I'd miss
the Edgar Allan Poe story

27:03.752 --> 27:05.928
"The Cask of Amontillado."

27:12.805 --> 27:14.328
In it...

27:15.590 --> 27:18.158
...Fortunato crosses
the wrong guy,

27:18.201 --> 27:20.203
and gets bricked up
behind a wall.

27:29.473 --> 27:31.388
[laughs softly]

27:31.432 --> 27:32.651
It's a safe.

27:37.481 --> 27:39.135
Uh, no.

27:39.179 --> 27:40.310
No, Tiffany, Tiffany
wouldn't send me

27:40.354 --> 27:42.182
all the way down here
without the key.

27:42.225 --> 27:43.270
You're right.

27:44.880 --> 27:47.404
Because she wanted
to turn back time.

27:47.448 --> 27:49.450
This is the last puzzle.

27:51.234 --> 27:54.194
Tiffany saw you at 8:12
the night it happened,

27:54.237 --> 27:55.674
you said, right?
Right.

27:56.718 --> 27:58.067
Okay.

27:58.111 --> 27:59.982
It's like a combination lock.

28:00.026 --> 28:02.419
We need to put in
another time. To when?

28:02.463 --> 28:03.856
Uh, the... uh,
the night it happened?

28:03.899 --> 28:06.162
Uh, April 28, 4/28.

28:13.909 --> 28:15.128
[gasps]

28:21.700 --> 28:23.919
[glass shatters]

28:25.181 --> 28:27.183
Okay, you heard that, right?

28:27.227 --> 28:28.576
[thunder rumbling]

28:37.150 --> 28:39.152
♪ ♪

28:49.597 --> 28:52.078
[panting]

28:52.121 --> 28:53.644
Must have been the wind.

28:55.298 --> 28:58.214
That's not gonna solve
your money problem.

28:58.258 --> 29:00.564
Yeah, well, it might help me
take my mind off of it.

29:07.049 --> 29:08.790
[thunder rumbling]

29:08.834 --> 29:10.836
♪ ♪

29:18.321 --> 29:22.630
Tiffany must have had a good
reason for hiding that so well.

29:22.673 --> 29:25.328
Well, let's get inside and...

29:28.070 --> 29:30.420
Have you decided about my offer?

29:41.867 --> 29:44.086
What offer is she talking about?

29:44.130 --> 29:46.567
[thunder rumbling]

29:46.610 --> 29:50.223
They're gonna drop all criminal
charges pending against me

29:50.266 --> 29:53.443
if I can help them make a case.

29:53.487 --> 29:55.489
Against you.

29:58.448 --> 30:00.668
Well...

30:00.711 --> 30:03.453
that's a good deal.

30:03.497 --> 30:05.455
[chuckles]

30:05.499 --> 30:10.504
So that's why you've been
digging into my past all day.

30:10.547 --> 30:13.681
Trying to save your own skin.

30:13.724 --> 30:15.509
Well, what'd you decide?

30:16.553 --> 30:18.425
Your case hinges on the theory

30:18.468 --> 30:21.123
that Nick wanted revenge
against Tiffany

30:21.167 --> 30:22.603
for testifying against him,

30:22.646 --> 30:24.474
that she was afraid of him,

30:24.518 --> 30:28.000
maybe even trying to buy him off
with some sort of package

30:28.043 --> 30:29.001
in a car.

30:29.044 --> 30:30.524
I have no choice

30:30.567 --> 30:31.699
but to prove you wrong.

30:33.744 --> 30:35.268
Your officers

30:35.311 --> 30:37.836
tossed all these books
on the floor,

30:37.879 --> 30:40.577
but they didn't
really look at them.

30:43.145 --> 30:45.147
Read the inscription.

30:46.670 --> 30:49.543
"Forgiveness is the key to redemption.

30:49.586 --> 30:52.459
Please forgive me. Tiffany."

30:52.502 --> 30:54.243
He may have hated her once,

30:54.287 --> 30:56.550
but that was before
they knew each other.

30:56.593 --> 30:58.030
Before they became friends.

30:58.073 --> 31:00.554
And Nick is not
the type of person

31:00.597 --> 31:02.861
to ever hurt somebody
he cares about.

31:04.253 --> 31:07.039
I can't explain to you
the level of trust between them,

31:07.082 --> 31:09.998
but you managed to get a look
at Nick's juvenile records.

31:11.521 --> 31:13.523
Check out the visitation logs.

31:15.264 --> 31:17.614
You'll see her name there
every week.

31:19.529 --> 31:21.662
Yes, he took a life once,

31:21.705 --> 31:24.795
but Tiffany learned that

31:24.839 --> 31:27.711
he would never do it again.

31:30.540 --> 31:32.673
That might be a consolation
for when you're arraigned

31:32.716 --> 31:36.590
for burglary and trespassing.

31:36.633 --> 31:40.550
For your sake,
I hope you're right.

31:56.436 --> 31:59.004
Are you afraid?

31:59.047 --> 32:00.875
You think I don't know
superstitions and rituals

32:00.919 --> 32:02.616
and communing with the dead?

32:02.659 --> 32:05.619
My mother made salt circles
around my high chair.

32:05.662 --> 32:09.101
It's different in the storm.

32:09.144 --> 32:11.538
[thunder rumbling]

32:11.581 --> 32:12.800
Restless spirits

32:12.843 --> 32:16.369
want a life,
and you've already been marked.

32:16.412 --> 32:18.980
Your friends have done the best
they could to protect you,

32:19.024 --> 32:22.418
but the protection only works
if you believe.

32:22.462 --> 32:24.116
[light creaking]

32:24.159 --> 32:25.378
Who are you?

32:25.421 --> 32:27.771
Better not leave that circle.

32:30.035 --> 32:31.471
Watch out![gasping]

32:34.561 --> 32:36.563
Oh. [gasping]

32:39.174 --> 32:41.481
Wait, wh-where did Rita go?

32:42.786 --> 32:43.744
Who?

32:43.787 --> 32:46.529
Rita.
Sh-She was just there.

32:46.573 --> 32:48.444
You all right, boss?

32:48.488 --> 32:50.185
Whoa! What did we miss?

32:53.623 --> 32:55.060
[panting]

33:00.065 --> 33:02.067
Tiffany Hudson gave me this.

33:04.156 --> 33:06.027
Finding it has

33:06.071 --> 33:08.856
forced me to confront things
about myself.

33:11.076 --> 33:13.687
I know you all had reason
to suspect that I'm a killer.

33:13.730 --> 33:18.518
And I know that reason's because
I've been hiding so much.

33:18.561 --> 33:22.261
I thought maybe
if we open it together,

33:22.304 --> 33:23.958
if I showed you,

33:24.002 --> 33:26.526
we could build some trust.

33:27.744 --> 33:29.703
You did kill somebody, though?

33:29.746 --> 33:32.053
Yeah.

33:34.099 --> 33:35.317
What happened?

33:39.104 --> 33:40.757
[sighs]

33:42.803 --> 33:44.587
His name was Austin.

33:46.546 --> 33:49.070
We used to go at it
on the football field,

33:49.114 --> 33:52.508
and it carried on to a party
I was at with a girlfriend,

33:52.552 --> 33:54.380
you know, just a friend.

33:55.424 --> 33:58.775
And Austin was drunk...

33:58.819 --> 34:01.735
high on something,

34:01.778 --> 34:05.434
and this time
he went after my friend,

34:05.478 --> 34:09.569
first with his words,
and then with his hands.

34:09.612 --> 34:13.181
And then he said,
"You got to go,

34:13.225 --> 34:14.748
but your girl stays."

34:14.791 --> 34:17.838
I couldn't leave her.

34:17.881 --> 34:20.884
And he wouldn't
let her go, so...

34:20.928 --> 34:22.886
I knocked him down.

34:22.930 --> 34:24.410
But not out.

34:24.453 --> 34:26.803
And he kept coming,

34:26.847 --> 34:29.197
so I kept going
and he went through

34:29.241 --> 34:31.243
a second-story
plate glass window.

34:34.942 --> 34:37.901
And he died...

34:37.945 --> 34:39.947
because of what I did.

34:45.518 --> 34:47.520
I killed Austin.

34:54.918 --> 34:57.747
And for the longest time,
I felt like a monster.

35:01.882 --> 35:04.624
I never wanted
to tell you this story.

35:09.977 --> 35:12.675
I was afraid it would
change things between us.

35:21.989 --> 35:23.643
I think we're past it now.

35:25.993 --> 35:28.561
[seagulls calling outside]

35:30.563 --> 35:32.826
What's important is who you are,

35:32.869 --> 35:34.697
not what you did.

35:37.700 --> 35:41.617
We should get back to work
before George starts yelling.

35:42.879 --> 35:45.186
George, I'm gonna take my break.

35:45.230 --> 35:47.797
Docking you again,

35:47.841 --> 35:49.799
but I'll see you after.

35:49.843 --> 35:52.150
You can show us the box later,

35:52.193 --> 35:54.152
but you better tell us
what's inside.

36:01.376 --> 36:04.249
[seagulls calling]

36:04.292 --> 36:05.902
[grunts]

36:09.123 --> 36:11.125
[buoy bell clangs softly]

36:20.134 --> 36:22.136
♪ ♪

36:42.504 --> 36:45.115
You chose this
over Karen's deal.

36:45.159 --> 36:47.205
I chose you.

37:02.045 --> 37:05.571
What are these?

37:05.614 --> 37:08.095
I think these are bearer bonds.

37:09.139 --> 37:10.837
They don't make these anymore.

37:10.880 --> 37:12.882
They're totally untraceable.

37:17.539 --> 37:20.977
Nick, this is almost $5 million.

37:21.021 --> 37:22.936
What?

37:22.979 --> 37:26.069
[chuckles]Wh... Why?

37:26.113 --> 37:28.202
To get it in your hands
without anybody knowing.

37:28.246 --> 37:30.509
Um, she wanted you
to have a fresh start.

37:30.552 --> 37:32.075
No. No. No way.

37:32.119 --> 37:33.120
No.

37:33.163 --> 37:34.991
This kind of money
brings trouble.

37:35.035 --> 37:37.385
I mean, people will think I-I-I
killed her to get to these.

37:37.429 --> 37:38.995
What am I supposed to do
with this?

37:39.039 --> 37:41.215
Keep them, obviously.

37:41.259 --> 37:43.696
How are you so calm? I get it.

37:43.739 --> 37:45.611
It-It's life-changing money.

37:45.654 --> 37:49.223
Is this even legal?
Did we just steal this?

37:49.267 --> 37:51.269
I am not going back to jail.

37:51.312 --> 37:54.272
Yes. No.

37:54.315 --> 37:56.622
And I know.

37:56.665 --> 37:58.319
In that order.

37:58.363 --> 38:00.016
[phone vibrates]

38:02.758 --> 38:04.325
It's Ace.

38:04.369 --> 38:06.501
He says he needs my help.

38:06.545 --> 38:07.937
Okay.

38:07.981 --> 38:10.331
Okay, okay.

38:10.375 --> 38:13.334
Is it? Because it doesn't
feel like it is.

38:13.378 --> 38:15.118
Well, it'll have to be.

38:15.162 --> 38:17.382
[sighs]

38:23.692 --> 38:26.042
I'll check in
with you later, okay?

38:31.265 --> 38:33.223
[crickets chirping]

38:33.267 --> 38:34.964
Hey.
Hi.

38:35.008 --> 38:36.618
Thanks for coming.

38:36.662 --> 38:38.664
I just didn't want
to embarrass her.

38:43.277 --> 38:45.888
I'll take it from here.Mm-hmm.

38:57.204 --> 38:58.423
Hi.

38:58.466 --> 39:01.426
Hi. Um...

39:03.341 --> 39:05.081
Come in.

39:12.001 --> 39:13.394
Um, it's...

39:13.438 --> 39:15.178
nicer when
the twinkly lights work.

39:15.222 --> 39:16.963
Uh, generator's flooded.

39:17.006 --> 39:20.053
Things aren't going so well
with your aunt, or...?

39:20.096 --> 39:23.143
Oh, you know how
families can be.

39:23.186 --> 39:24.971
Trust me, I get it.

39:25.014 --> 39:27.016
♪ ♪

39:29.149 --> 39:31.107
Nancy?

39:31.151 --> 39:33.936
You home?

39:33.980 --> 39:35.982
[sighs]

39:46.645 --> 39:48.734
The wine.

39:59.179 --> 40:01.094
[line ringing]

40:01.137 --> 40:02.617
NANCY [recorded]:
Sorry you missed me.

40:02.661 --> 40:04.227
Leave a message...[beeps]

40:09.755 --> 40:12.105
[water dripping]

40:14.368 --> 40:16.544
[skin crackles softly]

40:20.983 --> 40:23.203
This is just
a temporary arrangement.

40:23.246 --> 40:25.118
It's, you know... Hey,

40:25.161 --> 40:28.121
you really helped me out today.

40:28.164 --> 40:30.210
Do you think I could
return the favor?

40:30.253 --> 40:32.081
Oh, no, no, I'm fine, I'm fine.

40:32.125 --> 40:35.215
Yeah, I can see that.

40:35.258 --> 40:38.218
But until we can get
this place fixed up,

40:38.261 --> 40:40.133
you want to come stay with me?

40:42.178 --> 40:45.965
If it makes you feel
like we're even.

40:46.008 --> 40:47.401
Thank you.

40:47.445 --> 40:50.752
Okay, cool. I'll, um,
I'll pack my things. Great.

40:50.796 --> 40:54.277
NANCY:
Funny thing about rainstorms,

40:54.321 --> 40:56.149
they can cause a lot of damage,

40:56.192 --> 40:59.108
but they can also
wash away old debris

40:59.152 --> 41:02.677
and reveal what was
hidden underneath.

41:02.721 --> 41:06.681
This'll be great. If you want
to borrow clothes, go ahead,

41:06.725 --> 41:10.163
but obviously it works
both ways. Here you go.

41:10.206 --> 41:13.253
NANCY: And sometimes, as soon
as one storm passes,

41:13.296 --> 41:15.516
the clouds start to darken again

41:15.560 --> 41:17.431
and something like this pops up.

41:18.519 --> 41:20.521
A diamond ring

41:20.565 --> 41:23.306
that went missing
the night Tiffany died.

41:23.350 --> 41:25.308
Did I just invite a killer
to a sleepover?

41:51.770 --> 41:53.728
[woman screams, bell dings]

41:53.772 --> 41:55.730
[pencil scribbling]
